records.addlTxt: Outpatient Competency Status Update Letter; Received and Filed.

Defendant Rico Jermaine Nash Jr in court.  Attorney Ruby De Leon in court for Rico Jermaine Nash Jr.  Prosecuting attorney Olivia Simmons in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court on competency hearing. Competency hearing proceeded. Sworn for the State: Dr. Collins. Defendant has been found to be incompetent but likely to regain competency. Arguments heard from the State and defense counsel. Court adopts Dr. Collins findings and find the defendant to be incompetent but likely to regain competency. Court orders case SUSPENDED. Case adjourned to Branch 1.
Doctor's Report Return scheduled for January 6, 2023 at 02:30 pm.
Pretrial Services Supervision Report - 10-6-22, filed.  rmm

Attorney Ruby De Leon appeared in Court for Rico Jermaine Nash Jr. Defendant Rico Jermaine Nash Jr. appears in Court. Nate Kristian McClure appears for the State of Wisconsin.
CASE HEARD IN BRANCH 13 FOR BRANCH 1.
Case in court for return on doctors report. 
Parties in receipt of examiner's report dated 9/7/2022.  State does not dispute the findings, however the defense contests the report and request a competency hearing.  
Contested doctors report hearing affirmed with forensic unit. 
Case remains calendared in Branch 1.
Competency hearing scheduled October 6, 2022 at 8:30 a.m. in Branch 1.
Pretrial Services Supervision Report - 9-9-22, filed.  rmm

Attorney Ruby De Leon in court, defendant Rico Jermaine Nash not in court, in custody.  Katrina Voge appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for status conference.  Defendant's appearance is waived. Court is advised by the defense there is reason to believe the defendant is not competent to proceed.  Pursuant to Sec. 971.14 (2) Wisconsin Statutes, Court found probable cause and ordered defendant examined by the Forensic Unit.  Order for Examination, signed and filed.   Case remains calendared in Br. 01.  Doctor's Report Return scheduled for September 9, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Attorney Ruby De Leon in court, defendant Rico Jermaine Nash not in court, in custody.  
Abby Rockendorf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.
Hearing via Zoom.  Pretrial conference held.  Atty. De Leon has just been appointed and has not received discovery or an offer yet and requests a status date.  Case is adjourned to Br. 1.  Status conference scheduled for August 8, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered no contact with NFT
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Rico Jermaine Nash in court with attorney Stephen Andrew Sargent.  Defendant Rico Jermaine Nash in custody.  Thomas Hasle appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Rico Jermaine Nash appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Davila, Branch 1. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Defense request to be heard on bail if Defendant remains in custody.   
This hearing may be streamed live at the Court's discretion on https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/83289ee0-2326-3076-b9a3-4c551cf64527  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 29, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
